\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 39. H. spruneri} Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov. }{\b 2}({\b 8}): 112 (1849) ({\i H. perfoliatum }sensu Hayek pro parte, non L.). Stems 30-60 cm, erect, sometimes rooting at the base. Leaves 20-40(-60) mm, triangular-lanceolate or narrowly oblong, sessile, the uppermost sometimes with glandular auricles or with margin black-glandular-ciliate or denticulate. Sepals acute, black-glandular-ciliate and with numerous superficial black dots. Petals with black dots scattered over the whole surface. Capsule without dorsal vittae, but with numerous round, orange vesicles.{\i  Meadows and shady places. • W. part of Balkan peninsula, Istra, S.E. Italy.} Al Gr It Ju.
