\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 42. H. rumeliacum} Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  2}({\b 8}): 113 (1849). Stems 5-40 cm, erect or decumbent, branching but rarely rooting at the base. Leaves 6-35 mm, ovate-lanceolate or oblong to linear, sessile or shortly petiolate, the uppermost ones sometimes black-glandular-ciliate. Sepals acute, black-glandular-fimbriate or -ciliate and with numerous superficial black dots or streaks. Petals with black dots scattered over the whole surface. Capsule without dorsal vittae, with faint, round or elongated vesicles or almost smooth.{\i  Calcareous, stony places. • Balkan peninsula; one station in S. Romania}. Al Bu Gr Ju Rm.
